Completion.GoodAttempt: Good attempt! Try to plan your climb before starting to identify key handholds and create a strategy. Give it another go!
Completion.DevelopMentalGame: Nice try! Develop a strong mental game to stay focused and committed to each move, minimizing the risk of falling. Give it another go!
Completion.PracticeRestingPositions: Almost had it! Practice efficient resting positions to conserve energy for challenging sections. Give it another go!

Pathfinding.TrustGripStrength: Great effort! Trust your grip strength and commit to each move confidently. This will save energy!
Pathfinding.VisualizeSequence: Nice climb! Work on transitioning smoothly between holds to maintain a consistent pace throughout the climb.
Pathfinding.PacingStrategy: Good work! Practice quick decision-making to choose the most effective handholds without hesitation

Adjustments.StrengthenGrip: Awesome climbing! On your next attempt, try not to move your hand from where you first place it. This ensures you aren't wasting strength.
Adjustments.PrecisionPlacement: Great job! For next time, focus on precision when placing hands on holds to minimize the need for constant adjustments.
Adjustments.ReadRockTexture: Killer climb! Learn to read the hold to anticipate the type of grip required and reduce unnecessary micro-adjustments.

Efficiency.StrengthTraining: Great work up there! Next time, practice placing your hands once and not letting go until you make your next move.
Efficiency.BodyPositioning: Nice climb! Focus on body positioning to utilize core strength and reduce reliance on arm strength alone.
Efficiency.IncreaseDifficulty: Cool moves, climber! A more even distribution of your weight will reduce fatigue on your individual arms and legs.

CenterOfGravity.EngageCoreMuscles: Cool climb! Next time, try to engage your core muscles to maintain a stable center of gravity during movements.
CenterOfGravity.ControlledBreathing: Right on pal! Practice controlled breathing to aid in maintaining balance and coordination.
CenterOfGravity.PrecisePlacement: This isn't Footloose! Practice precise foot placement to ensure a solid and stable foundation.
CenterOfGravity.HipMovement: You looked great up there! For future climbs, keep your hips closer to the wall to reduce movement and rotation, and conserve energy.

Arm Bend.EnduranceDrills: Great work! Work on relaxing your arms when you're not making moves on the wall to minimize excess movement.
Arm Bend.ProperPositioning: Nice work! Try to keep your arms as straight as possible to reduce muscle fatigue and to climb more efficiently.
Arm Bend.DynamicMovements: Awesome climb! Incorporate dynamic movements to improve the adaptability of arm angles during climbs.
